## Quick Reference

| UI/UX Principle | SOLID Equivalent | Key Rule |
|----------------|------------------|----------|
| Atomic Design | SRP | One component, one responsibility |
| Design Systems | OCP & DRY | Reuse, don't repeat; extend, don't modify |
| 5 Planes of UX | DIP | Strategy drives design, not pixels |
| Gestalt Principles | ISP | Group related, separate unrelated |
| Hook Model | Engagement | Trigger → Action → Reward → Investment |
| User-Centered | Maintainability | Design for users, test assumptions |

---

## Always Remember

1. **Start Small**: Build atoms first, compose upward
2. **Reuse Everything**: Use design system, don't duplicate
3. **User First**: Strategy drives all design decisions
4. **Group Wisely**: Related items together, unrelated apart
5. **Engage Users**: Make actions easy, rewards variable, investment possible
6. **Test & Iterate**: Validate with users, improve continuously
